\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 In this sense, the indigenous-cholo
 peasantry antimining struggles challenge the circulation of the finance capital of the imperialists mining bourgeoisies,
 obstructing the production and circulation of mining commodities. The circuit of mining capital accumulation obstruction
 reduce the amount of surplus-value able for its realization as profit, reached by the sell of the mineral raw materials
 shaped as a volume of commodity-capital. If the time of circulation and organic finance capital composi\-tion are disrupted,
 the expected rate of super-profit decreases, and the gold-money\-commodity-capital appears as the preferred shape of capital
 to hold its surplus-value form, until the rate of super-profit increases enough to finish its circulation process as pure
 monetized total profit.}
\par
\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 In this point a psychological,
 if not substantial argument can hold. The economic rationality as is contextual, expect an opportunity, a sign of fortune
 which enhance its virtue. The window of opportunity should have the size correspondent to the sat\-isfaction of its ideological
 expectation about how much they (the top-layer capitalists syndicated in international bank state capitalists trusts holding
 the world-gold-capital) can increase its class-differentiation by the kind of opportunity for capital reproduc\-tion that
 can satisfy its will for power as the metamorphosis of becoming something differentiated, sublimated, alienated by the exploitation
 and domination of others as a mean and necessary-sufficient condition of their existence in the economic formation which
 they constitute as a top-world-imperialist-class integrated by the capitalists syndicated in international bank states capitalists
 trusts.}
\par
\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 This means became differentiated,
 alienated, sublimated, obviously not (only) from its world antagonistic classes (as history don\'92t repeats, its not a
 primitive accumula\-tion process of world-scale dispossession). That was already granted at a world-scale, since the inter-\'93nationa
l\'94 division of labor of the world-economy was completing or saturating its relations of production, while developed its
 concentration and centraliza\-tion processes inter-\'93nationally\'94. Of which are a part the horizontal decentralization
 of the Sino-American economic formations and their relations of production and cir\-culation, under breaking conditions
 of shared imperialism. As well as the imperialists wars and military interventions by which the geopolitical and geoeconomic
 contention develops their competition. The class-differentiation process is an intended result of }
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 the economic and political
 war in which the top-layer members of the international bank capitalists states trusts contend.}
\par
\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 The differentiation process
 is not driven by the production of surplus-value in the shape of commodity-capital, but by the circulation of overaccumulated
 world-capital funds as finance-money-capital into a reproduction process by a higher rate or profit. The resulted accumulation
 of augmented world-capital is expected to reach a quantita\-tive critical point in which a qualitative change of world-scale
 effects is achieved in the concentration of capital process which implied the preparation of the most crude of the imperialists
 wars. As in that manner the advancement of competitive and old forces of production are destroyed, and the new relations
 of production can be implanted to organize a world-economy for the reproduction of the world-capital of this top-layer of
 capitalists syndicated in the international bank state capitalists trusts ruling the geopolitical and geoeconomical contention.}
\par
\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 With not only consequences
 over the world-economy class structure and modes of production, but mainly over the natural, cultural, and historical conditions
 for our social reproduction. In their, atomized psychology the idea by which: a higher amount of capital advanced as finance
 capital into higher productive \'94national-economies\'94 is expected to result in a higher rate of profit. Indeed, the
 hoarding of gold, operates as a reserve fund which expresses the contradiction between the accumulation of monetized- money-capital
 and gold-money-capital in the national reserves of U.S. and China, particularly. It appears as if U.S. bank capitalists
 state trust is being ready for the transformation of a certain volume of gold-money-capital in monetized-capital beared
 in an inverse proportion by China\'92s bank capitalist state trust. And viceversa.}
\par
\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 Their will of sublimation,
 their will of power, drives its competitive voracity in a gold rush. Hoarded the fund of gold, they wait for an opportunity
 to finish its circula\-tion as money-capital. The reproduction of an immense volume of monetized-capital (accumulated in
 the shape of U.S. dollar hegemonic currency) under the existing con\-ditions impossible to be productively invested in the
 reproduction of their capital. From which point, a portion of its total profit, correspondent to the enterprise profit will
 circulate as advanced (finance) capital in the next stage of mining production, an\-other part will be paid as rent, another
 is accumulated by interest-profit. The part of enterprise-profit which is impossible to invest as advanced capital, is overaccumulated
 as a reserve fund of money-capital from which a minuscule portion can be expended by the top-layer capitalists bearing it.}
\par
\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 Meanwhile, the historical
 conditions expressed in indigenous-cholo antimining strug\-gles of Los Andes in direct contention to the most advanced economic
 formations of imperialism world-economy, also evidence an advanced development of the historical process of class struggle.
 The antimining struggles have effects on a world scale on the decrease in the rate of profit due to the obstruction of the
 time of circulation in the transformation of surplus-value into profit, in addition to disturbing the organic composition
 of the capital advanced by the mining circuit of reproduction, in the mon\-etary hoarding of gold by the bank capitalists
 state trusts. They have an antisystemic effect on the circuit of extended capital accumulation of the imperialist bourgeoisies
 by blocking the expansion of their extractive mining frontier, and obstructing the production and trade of minerals in general,
 and gold in particular.}
\par
