 national reserves, as its superiority in monetary holdings compared to the U.S. (Figure 2) required a balance in proportion
 to its monetary-gold holdings (Figure 3) to overcome the U.S. dollar as hegemonic currency, and intensified its capital
 production by gold mining in national contexts under which the situation of Sino-American shared imperialism remains, as
