\pard\plain\qj\fi260\wrapdefault\s64\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid
{\cs20\lang1033\langfe1033\f1\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs22\afs22\ul0 In the current critical
 juncture of capitalism\'92s systemic chaos (Arrighi and Silver 1999), antimining struggles in Los Andes and Latin America
 take an anti-imperialistic and antisystemic role. To initiate a fifth systemic cycle of accumulation, the top-layer of capitalists
 syndicated in the international bank capitalist state trusts requires in\-vesting the enormous magnitude of money-capital
 already accumulated in the branches of industry where larger profits can be obtained. Until new industries or future tech\-
nological innovations could offer higher super-profit, their productive capital will be allocated intensively in the branches
 of industry they already know can provide the highest rate of profit, as mining and gold mining in particular. A new material
 expan\-sion phase is a necessary condition for another cycle of financial expansion (Arrighi, 1994), but at this time the
 extended accumulation circuit mechanism could be reaching its natural, cultural and historical limits. Not only climate
 change but also historical change constrains and obstructs capitalism reconstitution at the present.}
